---
// One idea: nobody remembers the calm passages — it's the storms, the trials,
// that get gilded into the story worth telling.
---
<svg width="560" height="200" viewBox="0 0 560 200" role="img" aria-labelledby="storms-t">
  <title id="storms-t">A voyage across the page. The calm stretches are drawn faint and flat, nearly forgotten. The storm stretches rise into vivid, gilded peaks — marked as the parts that become the story.</title>
  <path class="ink hair" d="M30 120 L 130 120" opacity="0.35" />
  <text class="hand-label" x="46" y="140" font-size="12" opacity="0.5">calm (forgotten)</text>
  <path class="ink spine" d="M130 120 C 150 70, 180 74, 200 118" stroke="var(--poppy)" />
  <path class="ink hair" d="M230 120 L 320 120" opacity="0.35" />
  <path class="ink spine" d="M320 120 C 342 58, 376 64, 398 116" stroke="var(--poppy)" />
  <path class="ink hair" d="M428 120 L 520 120" opacity="0.35" />
  <circle class="port-fill" cx="165" cy="78" r="3" /><circle class="port-fill" cx="358" cy="70" r="3" />
  <text class="hand-label hand-label--accent" x="150" y="52" font-size="13">the storms become the story</text>
  <text class="hand-label" x="360" y="146" font-size="12" opacity="0.5">calm (forgotten)</text>
</svg>
